    "schema:description": "Metadata harvested from Borealis by the EarthCube GeoCodes catalog using Gleaner. The original record was serialized as Croissant (http://mlcommons.org/croissant/1.0) with the schema.org namespace incorrectly set to https://schema.org/ (should be http://schema.org/). The record was converted from Croissant to CDIF-friendly schema.org JSON-LD following the mapping in ConvertToCroissant.py: @type sc:Dataset changed to Dataset, cr:FileObject distributions changed to DataDownload, Croissant-specific context prefixes (cr:, rai:, sc:) and properties (cr:md5, cr:citeAs) removed, and @vocab corrected to http://schema.org/. Converted to CDIF Discovery profile: Property names prefixed with schema: namespace per CDIF convention; @context converted from @vocab style to explicit CDIF prefix declarations (schema, dcterms, dcat, prov); @type normalized to array format with schema: prefix; schema:identifier added from @id; schema:license wrapped in array; Distribution @type values normalized to arrays with schema: prefix; All nested @type values converted to arrays with schema: prefix. Round 2 CDIF fixes: subjectOf @type changed to [\"schema:Dataset\"] per CDIF CatalogRecord schema; subjectOf @id added (required by schema); schema:creator wrapped in @list to preserve author order per CDIF convention; Distribution encodingFormat wrapped in arrays; fileSize renamed to schema:contentSize; schema:spatialCoverage wrapped in array; spatialCoverage strings converted to Place objects.",
